<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1636,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1671,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</emphasis>
New for 
<collectingCountry box="[458,531,1671,1694]" name="Ghana" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Ghana</collectingCountry>
. This is the most widely distributed species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1228,1672,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudothyretes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1228,1672,1695]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Pseudothyretes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is known from several countries from the west (
<collectingCountry box="[524,670,1706,1729]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
) to the east (
<collectingCountry box="[827,900,1706,1729]" name="Kenya" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Kenya</collectingCountry>
) of equatorial Africa. The records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1366,1435,1706,1729]" name="Ghana" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Ghana</collectingCountry>
complete the scattered distributional data regarding the western part of its range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1636,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1775,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is very easy to determine after examination of the male genitalia. Elongate, narrow and slightly widened terminally lobes of uncus are unknown in any other member of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Przybylowicz" box="[1128,1342,1810,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" refString="Przybylowicz, L. (2009) Thyretini of Africa. An Illustrated Catalogue of the Thyretini (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae: Syntominae) of the Afrotropical Region. Entomonograph Series, Vol. 16, Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 170 pp." type="book" year="2009">
Przybyłowicz 
<number box="[1284,1342,1810,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
